Global 5G Infrastructure in Healthcare Market Insights
5G Infrastructure in Healthcare Market size was valued at USD 1.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 8.7 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 24.5% from 2024 to 2030.

5G Infrastructure in Healthcare Market Overview
The global 5G infrastructure in healthcare market was valued at approximately USD 5.8 billion in 2024 and is expected to expand at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 38.4% from 2025 to 2032. This significant growth is driven by the increasing demand for high-speed connectivity in healthcare facilities, enabling remote patient monitoring, telemedicine, and the integration of IoT devices. The market is seeing rapid adoption of 5G technologies to improve healthcare efficiency, enhance real-time data transmission, and support critical applications such as robotic surgery and augmented reality in medical procedures.

